          <msContents>
            <summary>Observances (vrata) related to food, bathing, and other rites, performed for the worship and veneration of the Hindu goddess Pārvatī as well as a deity in the form of the planet (graha) named Budha (Mercury). Performed on the eighth day of the month of Vaiśākha. Presented as a conversation between the Hindu deity Kṛṣṇa and the legendary king Yudhiṣṭhira.</summary>
            <textLang>In Sanskrit</textLang>
            <msItem>
              <title>Budhāṣṭamīvrata</title>
              <colophon>Colophon: iti śrībhaviṣyottarapurāṇe kṛṣṇayudhiṣṭhirasaṃvāde budhāṣṭamivratakathāsamāptā // (f. 10r).</colophon>
            </msItem>
